Webhooks

The platform delivers event notifications to the HTTPS endpoint you configure in your project settings. Each delivery is a POST request whose body is a JSON envelope:

  {
    "id": "evt_8h2k...",
    "type": "invoice.paid",
    "created": 1716480000,
    "data": { "object": { ... } }
  }

To verify authenticity, compute an HMAC-SHA256 over the raw request body using your endpoint's signing secret and compare it, in constant time, to the value in the `X-Signature` header. Reject any request whose signature does not match. Respond with a 2xx status within 5 seconds to acknowledge receipt; otherwise the platform retries with exponential backoff for up to 72 hours.
